  "market_context": "Price in an uptrend entered a consolidation phase forming an ascending triangle with clear horizontal resistance and rising support (higher lows). A strong bullish momentum candle broke above resistance, triggering the trade setup.",
  "key_observation": "A green candle with a real body at least twice the size of the three preceding candles broke out of a well-defined ascending triangle near resistance, signaling strong bullish continuation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst identified a bullish momentum candle by comparing its real body size to at least three prior candles, confirming it was ≥2× larger.",
    "Step 2: The analyst observed the price had formed an ascending triangle pattern with repeated retests of horizontal resistance and consecutive higher lows (rising support).",
    "Step 3: The analyst confirmed the breakout occurred at the resistance level, with the momentum candle closing above it.",
    "Step 4: For entry, the analyst recommended entering at the close of the momentum candle (no wait for further confirmation).",
    "Step 5: For stop-loss, the analyst placed it just below the most recent swing low (the last low of the ascending triangle), citing market structure alignment.",
    "Step 6: For target, the analyst projected profit using the vertical height of the ascending triangle measured from breakout point upward."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "The bullish momentum pattern is most reliable when it occurs within a clear chart pattern like an ascending triangle; entry at candle close, stop below recent low, and target using triangle height yields favorable risk/reward.",
